description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about palliative care? Do you want to work for an organisation where you have the time to truly deliver high quality care? Then this may be the role for you, we at Rennie Grove have a rare opportunity to join our Herts Hospice at Home team, with roles in the Dacorum and St Albans &amp; Harpenden teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role of Hospice at Home Nurse is in place to provide specialist palliative nursing care to patients and families within their own home. You will be visiting individuals in their own homes so a car and driving licence will be essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll need to demonstrate your abilities in the following areas:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First level registered General Nurse desirably with a module in palliative care or cancer care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current post registration experience at Band 5 or above carrying out general or specialist nursing care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience of effective team working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent judgement and good decision making skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess, plan, deliver and evaluate nursing care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Caring and empathetic approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to Rennie Grove purpose.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;asupportive environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;personal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;flexible working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;opportunities to volunteer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;generous annual leave entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC registration fees paid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;passionate team with quality at the heart of what we do.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;At Rennie Grove Hospice Care, we’re all about making every moment matter for our patients and families, and you can play your part in that. We provide care and support for adults and children diagnosed with cancer and other life-limiting illness, and their families, visiting day and night. It’s important work and, to make it all happen, we need talented and passionate people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;ARE YOU READY TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE? Click ‘Apply Now’….&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat abouth this role contact Judith Moore, Head of Nursing &amp; Patient Services Herts on 07393 232724.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12 November 2020 at 12 noon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews: 25 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
